annotation.TEXT: And now it's boss time again! And this time, I'm going to make sure I don't get glitched into the wall!
BGM: Castlevania 2 - Bloody Tears
Oh, what hit me? Must've been the Blargg as he was returning to his original position. Meh, no big deal, because there's another mushroom right there... maybe.
BGM: Golden Axe - Ending Credits - Sutakora, Sassa!
Ack! Okay, so Thwomps can hide in barrels on the ceiling. Good to know. (I'm surprised the Thwomp isn't ◢-shaped.)
Oh, man. Looks like the Chilly Shroom mentioned in this level's name is coming up.
Yep, I made the right choice, since I would've missed that Yoshi head otherwise.

Oh, geez. Really? That might explain why I was using normal-looking slopes to run up certain walls. So why were the wall triangles banned? Did Google start making unwanted changes to the Mushroom Kingdom and the wall triangles complained?
Alright, now since this is just a one-world demo, I'm betting Triangle Fortress is the last level, so I'm going to play it now!
Shut up, clock.
I take it that slope in the lower-left is not a wall triangle, or else it would've launched the shell right back towards me.
Hello, and welcome back to some more hat searching! Let's check out this supposedly cold mushroom...
Wait, when did I get a wall triangle in my reserve box? Oh, this is a nice wall triangle, which acts like a mushroom.
At least that wasn't really a problem, but it was still kind of funny how it "appeared" to be a problem.
Okay, this yellow koopa is definitely odd. It's not walking as fast as it should be.
Bah. Just 30. Well, that's probably still good for this particular goal, but it still hurts my goal tape average.
I gotta check something here...
BGM: Super Mario 64 - Cave Dungeon
Okay, there's a wall triangle, and it's acting like a Ninji. Oh, I get it. The wall triangles were evil duders all along! Then they all must die!
I still have a yellow mushroom in my reserve slot. However, it's just an ordinary mushroom. (Yeah, so the red palette must've been changed to yellow here for some reason.)
Demo count: 7 Glitched demos: 1
Meh. Nuts to the shell here.
Also, the normally red mushrooms and 1-up symbols are yellow in this room too for some reason.
Whoa, found it.
Oh, look at this! We've got an obvious life-farming spot here, folks!
◢ush!
And now the shell looks dead, along with that other shell, but at least I didn't take a hit there.
Ack! What hit me? Oh, there's a spike there. How did I not see that initially? Was I too distracted by the Yoshi head up above?
Wait, if that elevator's on layer 2, then are those clouds in the background on layer 3?
Oh, and the offscreen ceiling is in effect, so jumping over that spike can be a little tricky.
I see that Pokey there. I just can't see its face until it moves out from behind that Tails155(TM)-brand dirt wall. Move faster, Pokey!
No, it doesn't look like it. Also, does that shell look a little weird to you?
And now the shell looks normal again. It seemed to look weird to me while I was in the midpoint room, though.
And, it didn't spit out a coin when stomped. What about when it reenters its shell?
That was weird. Was there an enemy or projectile up there that I just didn't see? Let me quickly get back there...
Oh, brother. Even that switch has the mark of triangulation on it!
W-W-W-Whoa!!!
Whoops! That was accidental, but kind of cool.
BOING!
BGM: Animal Crossing - Rainy Day
Demo count: 6
...Is that it?
Well, I may have been bitten by a bullet back there, but if this is a power up block...
And now to play through the entirety of Triangle Fortress again at quadruple speed, because it lacked a midpoint (unless I just simply failed to find the midpoint).
Welp, no block factory this time.
Wow, that thing was actually fully functional! That's really interesting! (I was expecting that 32x32 springboard to either just be made of regular custom bounce blocks or teleport blocks.)
Alright, I've collected the third golden troll face.
I'll just take this Yoshi head now.
Whoa, careful.
Aw, but this block only gives me mushrooms regardless of my status. I doubt there are any fire flowers or capes in this hack.
Goal tape average so far: 110 / 3 = 36.667 stars each.
That unlocks Howater Cave. Is that supposed to say "Hot Water"? Or is "Howater" actually a thing in this hack?
Okay, that yellow koopa became a disco shell as expected, but I thought I noticed something odd about a previous yellow koopa.
Yep, there's the goal, without any obvious way to easily hit the tape near the top.
Maybe I should've just rewinded there, since that was cheap, but instead I'll just seek out power ups. The Chilly Shroom's namesake does function as a power up...
Whoa, is that a real wall triangle? No, because it would've launched the shell into the air if it was. This yellow wall triangle is just an ordinary slope.
Huh. I was expecting a Thwomp there. Maybe there was one but it failed to spawn due to the sprite limit? Who knows.
Whoa! I nearly got my noggin flowered!
Over there was the first Yoshi head. Nothing vital, but I want to collect all of those anyway.
Found midpoint, negating that dumb Chuck hit from a moment ago. Can either of these walls be climbed?
Argh. That mushroom platform up there is kind of an inconvenience for this.
Oh, what the?! I got glitched into the wall! Argh! (Also, I thought at first this was a Mouser boss, but I can tell now that it's a Clawgrip boss.)
Okay, I definitely see this spike right next to the Wiggler here.
Okay, so we've got water here, and it's of the gravity-defying variety. (Maybe "Howater" is the name of such water?)
Looks like a layer 2 elevator. Guess I gotta dodge a couple spikes while I ride this thing down.
Alright, I got a reserve mushroom... maybe.
BGM: Whacky Whistlin', by Jascha (played at 150% speed)
I've noticed that the coins are now in various colors, but they're not worth different amounts like in certain other hacks. They're still worth just 1 coin each.
And there's another triangle power up right there.
Bonus game average so far: 5 / 1 = 5 1-ups each.
Hey, no kicking troll faces at me.
Yeah, it's gotta be a Goomba.
D'oh!
Nah, unfortunately, they're neither flammable nor inflammable. Oh, well.
Whoa, that's a big springboard.
Oh, now that I'm fiery, can I open the fridge or burn the table in Luigis House?
Oh, I should totally try to block factory this thing.
Whoa, is that Chuck kicking flowers at me? That's weird. However, I'm sure those flowers won't give me fireball-shooting powers!
I don't know why I did that with the shell. I must've just felt like it.
Oh, I'm gonna need another ◢-switch.
Huh, how do I reach that Yoshi head?
Ooh, there's a secret passage through this bullet cannon! (The koopa kind of gave it away.)
Okay, so there's the goal. Let's see if I can get some good timing with the bullets here.
Wait, why did I just die?
Ha, gotcha. The big guy frowns whenever he's hit.
Nope, there's nowhere else to go, so I guess I'm done... or am I?
Okay, going to the right is obviously one-way, so I'll try the pipe on the left first.
Ha! I was expecting you that time, Thwomp!
Hmm... Well, I don't see any water yet (Maybe it meant "No Water"?), and I can run up this short wall to the left for some reason.
Looks like I'll need to find a T-switch to reach that big springboard.
Yep.
And that appears to be it. No new levels opened up, and I don't think I can go anywhere else, but I'll try pressing every direction while on every level dot, just in case...
Umm... Okay...
Move faster, Triangley, so I can kill you with my head because my butt's on the ground! Heck, yeah!
Apparently, the power of the Chilly Shroom makes it seem like there's an obstruction there, preventing me from backtracking.
And there it is.
Alright, that'll do. I won't spend forever there.
Goal tape average so far: 140 / 4 = 35 stars each.
Move faster, Triangley!
Oh, I see. This pointy part of the terrain here must be like a spike/muncher, which I hit last time without noticing its pointiness, likely due to the status bar being in the way.
A Blargg in perfectly swimmable water. Sure, why not. And, he's guarding the second golden troll face, which I obviously want to collect.
No disco. So, this guy is actually either a green koopa or a red koopa (I want to say red). I wonder why the change to the koopa's palette though?

I didn't mean to actually enter the trippy dimension there, but I was late on the pause button press. Hmm... Isn't there a place where I can get a quicker power up? I don't remember. Let's try Sky Garden.
Yay, I got all of the Yoshi heads and got a yellow 1-up!
BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! WOO! BURN! TRI FORMATION! BURN TO THE GROUND!
I see that muncher embedded in the ceiling, and I bet it will OMNOMNOM me if I bump into it! Of course, it would've helped if I didn't bump into the side of the Chuck...
Hmm... I kind of overshot with that one over there. Oh, well. I guess we'll ignore it for the rest of the battle.
Gotta continue watching out for those spikes.
And, it's boss time, against the wall triangle king himself!
Ah! That Thwomp was there this time! (Probably because I didn't have that triangle shell to hit the sprite limit with this time.)
No, I might still be trippin', because there's a wall triangle Wiggler!
That was neat how I bounced around on that leftover triangle when I won there! Thank goodness it didn't glitch-kill me again in the process!
Huh. I can no longer backtrack here. Maybe back when I was trippin', I failed to perceive that wall there, and that allowed me to get through... Wait, what?
Oh, this ? block's actually a fire flower block! Neat. Now I can burninate stuff!

You know... Actually, this isn't so bad. Some of the colors are changing, and the background is wavy, but at least it's not like when you touch fuzzy and get dizzy in Yoshi's Island, where the terrain gets all wavy, and Yoshi controls like a drunk.
I wonder if Mario could've carried that huge springboard around if it wasn't obstructed by walls on both sides of it... Probably not.
Well, I'm sure I'll need this ◢-switch soon.
Okay, that troll face that just flew past me was obviously a Bullet Bill. But, what is the other one? I think it's a Goomba.
Whoa! Okay, I think the trippy effects have worn off now.
And there's the last Yoshi head, so the goal must be just up ahead.
Uhh... What the heck just happened? This is weird... That wasn't a Tanetane Island mushroom, was it?
◢ush!
And now, ludricous speed bonus game... maybe.
Tush! Ooh, T-switch jump!
A wall triangle raft? Oh, that's just silly.
Well, that's not a very good first bonus game of this hack. (Weird sound effect is from Mario Paint.)
Remove the first "i" in "confiusion". Also, should "Chillyshroom" be separated into two words?
Aha!
Oh! Through a fragile block! That's how!
Whoa, that was an unexpected screen transition (especially since there was a visible enemy to the right). Did I just recover from the Chilly Shroom again?
BGM: Nightwish - Ever Dream
This one's a Goomba, and that one's a shell.
Good thing I was big, because otherwise I wouldn't have been able to get this golden troll face, and it would've been like, "Problem?".
I wasn't really fond of that timing. Also, I think my 1-up mushroom got permanently stuck in the ceiling, since there's no upside-down slope for it to fall through this time. That's a bummer.
To be continued...
